         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">York Nursery Kew ¶ Augt 1st /84 ¶ Dear Baron ¶  ¶ You will of course have got my letter with the description of the Phaijus, ¶  about as near natural. ¶  You mention the Rhizome the size I cannot exac...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">84.08.01</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">From James Roberts</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">RB MSS M136, Library, Royal Botanic Gardens Melbourne.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <note xml:id="ftn1" type="footnote" n="1">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">File annotated by T. B. Muir on 24 March 1977: 'James Roberts received specimens from Consul Layard, New Caledonia, (&amp; perhaps from others) in ±1883. He cultivated these, and one of them was described by Mueller (<seg style="">
                        <hi rend="underline">Phajus robertsii</hi>
                     </seg>) in <seg style="">
                        <hi rend="underline">S. Sci. Rec</hi>
                     </seg>. <seg style="">
                        <hi rend="underline">3</hi>
                     </seg>: 265 (Dec. 1883)' i.e. B3.12.05.</p>
               </note>York Nursery Kew<note xml:id="ftn2" type="footnote" n="2">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">Melbourne.</p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">Augt 1st /84</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">Dear Baron</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>You will of course have got my letter with the description of the <name key="Phaijus">Phaijus</name>,<note xml:id="ftn3" type="footnote" n="3">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <seg style="font-style: italic; ">Phaius</seg>? Frequently written as <seg style="font-style: italic; ">Phajus</seg> by M.</p>
               </note> about as near natural.<note xml:id="ftn4" type="footnote" n="4">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">See J. Roberts to M, 30 July 1884.</p>
               </note> You mention the Rhizome the size I cannot exactly give but it near enough when I say that is like common ginger only not so knotty it has no distinct bulb at all so far however as my plants are concerned <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">perhaps if I say it is like a Bamboo root I shall be nearest what it is</hi>
               </seg>, but smaller in proportion to the two plants.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>As regards the naming of this plant after me I think it is a right I can claim in this respect.<note xml:id="ftn5" type="footnote" n="5">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">M described <seg style="font-style: italic; ">Phajus robertsii</seg> in B83.12.05.</p>
               </note> Mr Layard did not know anything about it nor did he make any special mention beyond the fact of his picking it up while looking for ferns for me &amp;c &amp; in fact he had forgotten it altogether even when I mentioned it as having flowered he did not know wether<note xml:id="ftn6" type="footnote" n="6">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">whether?</p>
               </note> it was an Orchid or not at the time. I should like though that the next that turns up new should be called after him I have yet 3 or 4 Orchids from N C<note xml:id="ftn7" type="footnote" n="7">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">New Caledonia.</p>
               </note> yet to bloom</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>hoping you are daily improving</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I beg to express a hope that you will soon get better from your long illness</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">Regardfully yours</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>James Roberts</p>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <name key="Phaijus">Phaijus</name>
            </p>
         </div>
